format: A frequency data frame with 80 observations on the following 5 variables.
reference: The table contains a fair number of 0 counts.
description:
Description
The Alligator data, from Agresti (2002), comes from a study of the primary food choices of alligators 
in four Florida lakes. Researchers classified the stomach contents of 219 captured alligators into five categories: 
Fish (the most common primary food choice), Invertebrate (snails, insects, crayfish, etc.), 
Reptile (turtles, alligators), Bird, and Other (amphibians, plants, household pets, stones, and other debris).
title: Alligator Food Choice

parameters.sex: a factor with levels female male
parameters.size: alligator size, a factor with levels large (>2.3m) small (<=2.3m)
parameters.lake: a factor with levels George Hancock Oklawaha Trafford
parameters.food: primary food choice, a factor with levels bird fish invert other reptile
